      "content": "I'm really sorry to hear you're feeling this way. High stress, physical exertion, and possible hyperglycemia can intensify symptoms. Before you take any insulin, it would be wise to test your blood sugar levels to check if they are indeed high. If they are, then you may need to consult with your healthcare provider about adjusting your insulin dose at this time. Always remember to follow your treatment plan and consult with them before making any changes. Sugar tablets or balanced snacks could also help stabilize your blood sugar levels until you are able to contact them. Stay safe, take it easy, and prioritize your health.",
