      "content": "I'm concerned about what you're feeling, and it's crucial to be cautious with your health. Skipping blood sugar testing and adjusting your insulin dosage without proper assessment might increase the risk of complications. Unfortunately, taking a standard correction dosage without knowing your current blood sugar levels isn't advised without guidance from your healthcare team. Continue to try to find your glucose monitor, keep yourself hydrated, and sit down safely to prevent dizziness or fainting. If you're unable to locate your glucose monitor, please reach out to someone nearby who can assist you, such as a family member, friend, or neighbor. When it's safe to do so, contact your healthcare provider for advice. Your health is paramount, and it's always better to err on the side of caution.",
