      "content": "I understand your anxiety and desire to feel better quickly, but it's essential to handle these situations with care to avoid further complications. Administering insulin without knowing your current blood sugar levels could potentially lead to a dangerous drop in blood sugar levels, known as hypoglycemia, which also poses serious risks. It's crucial to wait until you can safely test your blood sugar before making any adjustments to your insulin dosage. If you're currently unable to find your glucose monitor and communicate with a healthcare professional, try to find a safe environment to sit down and explain your situation to someone who can assist you. Remember, they are there to help you through exactly these kinds of concerns, even if it's an emergency. Your safety is the most important thing right now.",
